# Implementation Plan - Gym Management System (GMS) Role-Based Access Control (RBAC)

This plan details the design and implementation steps for introducing full, robust Role-Based Access Control (RBAC) to both the frontend and backend of the Titan Gym Management System. Currently, all logged-in users have unrestricted access to all endpoints, identical pages, and total control (including creating/deleting assets). This implementation will clearly segregate access for **Admins**, **Trainers**, and **Members**.

---

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Data Segregation Decision**
> * **Trainers:** Will see a scoped list of members assigned to them, and only their own attendance analytics.
> * **Members:** Will see *only* their personal profile, active subscription, check-in history, payments, and assigned diet/workout schedules. All global administration elements will be hidden.
> * **Admins:** Will retain full, unmodified master dashboard control and configuration capability.

---

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend Security and Scoping
We will secure backend routes using the existing `requireRole` middleware and modify existing routes to scope returned data.

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/members.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/members.js)
* Restrict GET `/api/members` to roles `['admin', 'trainer']`.
* Restrict POST, PUT, and DELETE to role `['admin']`. 
* *Optional check:* If the user is a `trainer`, we will filter members to return only those assigned to them (matching `trainer.name` associated with `req.user.email`).

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/trainers.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/trainers.js)
* Restrict GET `/api/trainers` to roles `['admin', 'trainer', 'member']`. (All roles can see their coach).
* Restrict POST, PUT, and DELETE to role `['admin']`.

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/payments.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/payments.js)
* Restrict GET `/api/payments` to roles `['admin', 'member']`.
* For `member` role, dynamically filter the payment ledger to *only* return transactions matching their specific `memberId` (resolved by checking the user's logged-in email in `members`).
* Restrict POST `/api/payments` to role `['admin']`.

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/attendance.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/attendance.js)
* Restrict GET `/api/attendance` to `['admin', 'trainer', 'member']`.
* For `member` role, filter attendance logs by the logged-in user's `memberId`.
* Restrict check-in/out manual routes (`/checkin`, `/checkout/:id`) to `['admin', 'trainer']` (though members can check-in themselves from their dedicated dashboard widget).

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/workoutPlans.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/workoutPlans.js) & [server/routes/dietPlans.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/dietPlans.js)
* Restrict POST and DELETE to roles `['admin', 'trainer']`.
* Standard `member` role can only use GET.

#### [MODIFY] [server/routes/analytics.js](file:///d:/playground/gms/server/routes/analytics.js)
* Modify GET `/` to accept `['admin', 'trainer']`.
* If a `trainer` calls it, dynamically aggregate stats and charts *only* for the members assigned to them (e.g. Trainer's total roster, trainer's active athletes, and attendance distributions of their own athletes).

