### 2. Frontend Navigation Guards and Routing

#### [NEW] [src/components/layout/ProtectedRoute.jsx](file:///d:/playground/gms/src/components/layout/ProtectedRoute.jsx)
Create a route guard component that verifies if the user is authenticated and has an allowed role. If they do not, it redirects them to the `/dashboard`.

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import { Navigate } from 'react-router-dom';
import { useSelector } from 'react-redux';

export const ProtectedRoute = ({ children, allowedRoles }) => {
  const { user, isAuthenticated } = useSelector(state => state.auth);

  if (!isAuthenticated) {
    return <Navigate to="/login" replace />;
  }

  if (allowedRoles && !allowedRoles.includes(user?.role)) {
    return <Navigate to="/dashboard" replace />;
  }

  return children;
};
```

#### [MODIFY] [src/App.jsx](file:///d:/playground/gms/src/App.jsx)
Integrate `<ProtectedRoute />` across restricted dashboard sub-routes:
* `/members` -> `['admin', 'trainer']`
* `/trainers` -> `['admin']`
* `/payments` -> `['admin', 'member']`

